<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-28T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/5299:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-28T16:00:00+01:00">August
                                        28, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received August 28—3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Referring to my telegram of this morning, Husson, Governor General of
                                French Equatorial Africa, physically attacked by pro-De Gaulle
                                faction escaped to Leopoldville and has sought refuge with the
                                Governor General of the Belgian Congo. The whole of French
                                Equatorial Africa has now declared for De Gaulle. De Larminat has
                                gone to Brazzaville.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>